Seiger <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sethnicity>Sethnicity</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/2/02 7:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=980.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Translating &quot;Don't let my appearance fool you...&quot;</span><hr size=1> The real trick with Japanese is that unlike English, it's VERY important who's speaking, and to whom they're speaking.<br>
<br>
For example, if this phrase is coming from a cute-looking schoolgirl, it'd have cutesy Japanese.<br>
If, on the other hand, it's coming from a nerdy looking hogh-school boy, it'd have mock-tough written all over it.<br>
<br>
So... let's hear the CONTEXT of the phrase, so the translation will come out right. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seiger@polykarbonbbs>Seiger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/5/02 4:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=980.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Need Translation</span><hr size=1> Ah... context matters. <br>
<br>
<br>
It's my 'alter ego' that's speaking. He's dressed like the average guy, with a big shirt and baggy jeans. He looks very, very peaceful, but he's a real bad*** at heart. No compassion whatsoever for those who can feel no guilt for wrongs they've commited. To put things simply, he's a ruthless killer under the name of good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sethnicity>Sethnicity</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/6/02 7:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=980.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The cynic in me...</span><hr size=1> My personal slant on this won't contribute positively to your project as it stands.<br>
<br>
If asked to translate for your unrepentant killer who enjoys an adrenalin rush without guilt when *ahem* punishing the wicked&quot;, I'd put my tongue firmly in cheek and say, <br>
<br>
&quot;Hai.  Mai neemu izu purejidento busshi.  Ai wanna meeku a waildo pawaaa gurabbu ando sasupendo hyuuman raituso, ando enjoi an adrenalin rasshi wailu killingu, batto fuiiiru morarii jaasutiifaido.&quot;<br>
<br>
The devil made me do it.<br>
<br>
Maybe someone else here will help you on this project...<br>
I think I like manga art for its occasionally realistic art, but its mental perspective is too often 2D to be really appealing.<br>
<br>
In the realistic world, there's no such thing as killing and enjoying it, and hiding behind &quot;He had it coming to him&quot; requires a really whacked perspective.<br>
That's why SPider Man comics and Sailor Moon have such broad appeal-- although their characters are essentially super-heros, with all the &quot;Clobberin' tiiiime&quot; attitude that implies, the characters contain a three-dimensionality that includes guilt, NOT enjoying killing-the-wicked, and seeking non-violent alternatives.  You'll also recall that the most interesting BatMan and Ironman episodes were the ones where THEY showed some depth, too... BatMan went morally neutral, and IronMan had a drinking problem.<br>
<br>
In short, a &quot;ruthless killer in the name of good&quot; is living in sociopath-land.  Not sure I wanna help him live there... the real world of confict resolution and rehabbing criminals peacefully is WICKED-hard, and that challenge is ALOT more fun adventure than &quot;clobberin' time&quot; comicland.<br>
<br>
OTOH, if this character is really your idealized vision of yourself empowered, violent, yet appreciated... I'm kinda glad it's on paper, not in the real world. *grin* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seiger@polykarbonbbs>Seiger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/7/02 7:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=980.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Still in need of help</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't say he's an idealized version of myself. e_e He's just THERE.<br>
<br>
Thanks for helping. ^_^ That thing on Bush was hilarious. But I see where you're coming from.<br>
<br>
He doesn't find killing fun. But he doesn't regret it. The point is that he's very dangerous, but looks like the kind of boy that you'd find looking through CDs at a Sam Goody's. <br>
<br>
&quot;H*ll takes many forms&quot; may be a better line... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sethnicity>Sethnicity</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.fureai-ch.ne.jp/~seth/pccat3.jpg " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/8/02 10:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=980.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oh... In THAT case... </span><hr size=1> Oh... In THAT case, let's take a swing at it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fuzakennayo.  Washya kureeyon shinchan rashii da kedo pikadon yori abunaiyo.&quot;<br>
<br>
This is really thick Hiroshima dialect (the Japanese equivalent of a Mafiosa Italian-Brooklyn accent), saying <br>
&quot;Don't f*** with me.  I may LOOK like Dennis the Menace, but I'm more dangerous than an A-bomb.&quot;<br>
<br>
(Crayon shinchan is a popular Japanese cartoon character who is the equivalent of our Dennis-the-Menace.  &quot;pikadon&quot; is Hiroshima slang for an A-bomb explosion. It literally means &quot;bright flash, boom&quot;-- sort of like &quot;Ka-BOOM&quot; in English.  Washya is a shortening of watakushi ha....a regional thing, like when Brooklyners say &quot;youse guys&quot; or Texans say &quot;y'all&quot;.)<br>
<br>
To make the thing less regionally accented, change washya to &quot;ore ha&quot;, and pikadon to genshibakudan.<br>
<br>
Kureeyon and pikadon would be in katakana, the rest in Hiragana. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sethnicity>Sethnicity</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.fureai-ch.ne.jp/~seth/pccat3.jpg " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/8/02 10:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=980.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oops -- fuzakennayo shoudl be zaken nayo.</span><hr size=1> Oops -- fuzakennayo should be zaken nayo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seiger@polykarbonbbs>Seiger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/9/02 4:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=980.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks!</span><hr size=1> A Japanese Dennis the Menace... there's a country's own answer to everything else, I guess. ^_^<br>
<br>
Thanks a lot for the help, Sethnicity. I appreciate it.<br>
<br>
<br>
-Seiger <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=980.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=980.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=980.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=980.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.threadControl?topicID=980.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=980.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=980.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="polykarbonbbsfrm18">PK-BBS Rule